It is okay , not to specify the table and column using the annotation if your column and table name **adhers to the Implicit naming strategy.**

&gt; The placement of the @Id annotation marks the persistence state access
&gt; strategy.The identifier uniquely identifies each row in that table. By 
&gt; default, the name of the table is assumed to be the same as the name
&gt; of the entity. To explicitly give the name of the table or to specify
&gt; other information about the table, we would use the
&gt; javax.persistence.Table annotation.A logical name can be either explicitly 
&gt; specified by the user (using @Column or @Table e.g.) or it can be
&gt; implicitly determined by Hibernate through an ImplicitNamingStrategy
&gt; contract.

